The voice on the other end was faint, distorted by time and the vast, desolate silence that lay between them. It was young, laced with confusion. It spoke of things that felt like ghosts â€“ traffic, busy streets, the mundane sounds of a world that had ceased to exist a century ago. Klaus leaned against the wall of the domeâ€™s observation deck, looking out at the bruised, grey sky and the skeletal remains of skyscrapers swallowed by the mutated flora. The contrast was jarring.

